main event: A resident of West Roxbury, Massachusetts reported seeing a bright, round object that glowed from the interior to the exterior and appeared like the head of a missile on fire.
interesting points: The object moved in an oval pattern and had a blurred shape.
The witness said the object was just like the ones described in newspapers as "flying saucers".
The Air Force concluded that the sighting was likely a meteor, and that the witness probably saw a high-flying jet aircraft.
The witness was interviewed by newspaper reporters about the sighting.
The Air Force did not consider the sighting to provide any data of significant technical value.
